---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Clad — Political Fact-Checks & Media Bias"
  description="What Clad is, how it grades political broadcasts for accuracy and bias, and how to get in touch."
>
  <article class="static-page">
    <h2 class="static-page__title">About Clad</h2>

    <p>
      Clad is an independent publication that fact-checks U.S. political news.
      We watch broadcast segments and reporting from across the spectrum, then
      publish a graded report card: an overall letter grade for accuracy, a
      factuality score, a measured read of political lean, and a plain-language
      explanation of <em>why</em> a segment earned its grade. Every report links
      back to its original source so you can verify it yourself.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">How we grade</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Letter grade &amp; factuality.</strong> Each report gets an
        overall grade (A+ to F) and a 0–100 factuality score reflecting how well
        its claims hold up against the available evidence.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Political lean.</strong> We rate lean as a magnitude and
        direction (for example, "78% right-leaning"), not a simple left/right
        label — and we explain the reasoning.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Key moments.</strong> Notable claims are pulled out individually
        and marked verified, disputed, missing context, or unsupported.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sources.</strong> Each report cites the material it draws on so
        the assessment is checkable, not just assertable.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Corrections</h3>
    <p>
      When we get something wrong, we issue a correction as a new post rather
      than silently editing the original. Accuracy is the whole point.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub" id="contact">Contact</h3>
    <p>
      Questions, tips, or corrections? Email the editor at
      <a href="mailto:editor@cladfacts.com">editor@cladfacts.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub" id="subscribe">Subscribe</h3>
    <p>
      Follow new reports with our feed:
      <a href="/rss.xml">subscribe via RSS</a>. Paste that link into any feed
      reader to get every new report as it publishes.
    </p>

    <p class="static-page__note">
      Clad's reports are editorial commentary, opinion, and analysis based on
      publicly available material, presented under fair use for commentary and
      criticism. Grades and verdicts assess the evidence and reporting, not the
      character of any person named.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
